### VoiceOwl API Testing
### Use this file with REST Client extension in VS Code or manually with curl

### 1. Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/api/health

### 2. API Info
GET http://localhost:5000/api

### 3. Create Mock Transcription (Part 1 Requirement)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/transcription
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "audioUrl": "https://example.com/sample-audio.mp3"
}

### 4. Get Transcriptions (Last 30 Days - Part 2 Requirement)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/transcriptions?page=1&limit=10

### 5. Get Transcription by ID
# Replace {id} with actual transcription ID from previous response
GET http://localhost:5000/api/transcription/{id}

### 6. Create Azure Transcription (Part 4 Requirement)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/azure-transcription
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "audioUrl": "https://example.com/sample-audio.mp3",
  "language": "en-US"
}

### 7. Create Azure Transcription with Different Language
POST http://localhost:5000/api/azure-transcription
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "audioUrl": "https://example.com/spanish-audio.mp3",
  "language": "es-ES"
}

### 8. Get Supported Azure Languages
GET http://localhost:5000/api/azure-languages

### 9. Test Invalid URL (Error Handling)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/transcription
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "audioUrl": "not-a-valid-url"
}

### 10. Test Missing audioUrl (Validation)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/transcription
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "someOtherField": "value"
}

### 11. Test Pagination
GET http://localhost:5000/api/transcriptions?page=2&limit=5

